doc.ContractDescription: A KEY PERIOD IN THE EVOLUTION OF COSMOLOGICAL STRUCTURE IS THE EPOCH OF REIONIZATION (EOR), WHEN EARLY POPULATIONS OF GALAXIES AND/OR QUASARS FORMED, EMITTED ULTRAVIOLET LIGHT, AND IONIZED `BUBBLES' OF NEUTRAL HYDROGEN GAS AROUND THEM. DETAILED OBSERVATIONS OF THE EOR WILL CONSTRAIN THE NATURE OF THE FIRST LUMINOUS SOURCES IN THE UNIVERSE, DESCRIBE THEIR IMPACT ON THE SURROUNDING INTERGALACTIC MEDIUM (IGM), AND FILL IN A SIGNIFICANT GAP IN OUR KNOWLEDGE OF THE HISTORY OF THE UNIVERSE. CURRENT OBSERVATIONS SUGGEST THAT THERE MAY IN FACT BE TWO SEPARATE EORS: AN EARLY EPOCH OF HYDROGEN REIONIZATION DURING WHICH HYDROGEN IS IONIZED, AND HELIUM IS SINGLY-IONIZED, BY STAR-FORMING GALAXIES, FOLLOWED BY A LATER EPOCH OF HELIUM REIONIZATION DURING WHICH HELIUM IS DOUBLY IONIZED BY BRIGHT QUASARS. THE GOAL OF THIS PROPOSAL IS TO MODEL BOTH HYDROGEN AND HELIUM REIONIZATION, TO COMPARE OUR THEORETICAL CALCULATIONS WITH EXISTING OBSERVATIONS, AND TO MAKE PREDICTIONS FOR UPCOMING DATA SETS. WE WILL MAKE USE OF RADIATIVE TRANSFER SIMULATIONS OF THE REIONIZATION PROCESS, AS WELL AS SEMI-ANALYTIC AND ANALYTIC MODELING, AND SOME ANALYSIS OF QUASAR ABSORPTION LINE DATA. WE PLACE SPECIAL EMPHASIS ON USING DATA AT THE TAIL END OF REIONIZATION, AND IN REIONIZATION'S IMMEDIATE AFTERMATH, TO CONSTRAIN MODELS AT HIGHER REDSHIFTS DURING THE BULK OF THE EOR. IN PARTICULAR, WE AIM TO IMPROVE MEASUREMENTS OF THE TEMPERATURE OF THE IGM FROM QUASAR ABSORPTION SPECTRA, AND TO COMPARE THEORETICAL MODELS WITH THESE MEASUREMENTS ALONG WITH MEASUREMENTS OF : OTHER STATISTICAL PROPERTIES OF HIGH REDSHIFT QUASAR ABSORPTION SPECTRA, HIGH REDSHIFT SURVEYS OF LYMAN-ALPHA EMITTING GALAXIES, AND HUBBLE SPACE TELESCOPE (HST) WFC-3 MEASUREMENTS OF LYMAN-BREAK GALAXY LUMINOSITY FUNCTIONS. THIS WILL HELP TO IMPROVE OUR UNDERSTANDING OF THE END OF REIONIZATION, AND SIGNIFICANTLY TIGHTEN OUR PREDICTIONS FOR UPCOMING OBSERVATIONS OF THE UNIVERSE AT STILL HIGHER REDSHIFT. IN ADDITION, CURRENT OBSERVATIONS SUGGEST THAT HELIUM IS DOUBLY IONIZED AROUND A REDSHIFT OF THREE, WHERE THERE IS A WEALTH OF EXISTING AND UPCOMING DATA. OF PARTICULAR INTEREST ARE FORTHCOMING OBSERVATIONS FROM THE COSMIC ORIGINS SPECTROGRAPH (COS) ONBOARD HST, AND THREE DIMENSIONAL MEASUREMENTS OF THE HYDROGEN LYMAN-ALPHA FOREST NEAR Z~3 FROM THE SLOAN DIGITAL SKY SURVEY-III (SDSS-III). WE WILL CONSIDER HOW TO MAKE BEST USE OF THESE OBSERVATIONS IN ORDER TO ELUCIDATE SOME OF THE DETAILS OF THE HELIUM REIONIZATION PROCESS, WHICH WILL IN TURN INFORM MODELS FOR QUASAR GROWTH AND DUTY CYCLES. THIS WILL ALSO PROVIDE A USEFUL TEST OF OUR REIONIZATION MODELS BEFORE DETAILED OBSERVATIONS OF HYDROGEN REIONIZATION AT HIGHER REDSHIFT BECOME AVAILABLE. THE PROPOSED WORK FOCUSES ON SOME OF NASA'S KEY SCIENCE GOALS, ESPECIALLY THOSE AIMED AT UNDERSTANDING THE FORMATION AND EVOLUTION OF THE FIRST GALAXIES, QUASARS, AND LARGE SCALE STRUCTURE. FURTHERMORE, OUR WORK WILL AID IN INTERPRETING DATA SETS FROM SEVERAL CURRENT AND FUTURE NASA-FUNDED MISSIONS INCLUDING: COS, THE JAMES WEBB SPACE TELESCOPE, THE PLANCK SURVEYOR, THE SWIFT SATELLITE, WFC-3, AND THE WILKINSON MICROWAVE ANISOTROPY PROBE. WE BELIEVE OUR WORK, PROVIDING A CLOSE COMPARISON BETWEEN THEORETICAL MODELS OF REIONIZATION AND EXISTING DATA, IS CRUCIAL FOR BEST INTERPRETING CURRENT OBSERVATIONS AND FOR REFINING OUR THEORETICAL MODELS IN PREPARATION FOR UPCOMING MEASUREMENTS. WE EXPECT THIS WORK TO SIGNIFICANTLY IMPROVE OUR UNDERSTANDING OF THE EOR AND EARLY STRUCTURE FORMATION.
